<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,520,687]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,474,520,546]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchitarsus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,474,520,546]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mesoconius anchitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[483,574,521,547]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[791,959,520,546]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitergum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[791,959,520,546]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. albitergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[967,1059,521,547]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1074,1193,520,547]" name="Colombia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Colombia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1261,1399,521,546]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cosanga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1261,1399,521,546]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. cosanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,285,556,582]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingCountry box="[306,410,555,582]" name="Ecuador" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
), with almost the same thoracic and leg pigmentation and very similar internal genitalia. The females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[502,682,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchitarsus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[502,682,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. anchitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[693,790,591,617]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, however, are strikingly different because of their greatly enlarged and flattened first fore tarsomere. The only available male specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1222,1399,626,652]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anchitarsus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1222,1399,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. anchitarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,280,661,687]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[542,709,661,687]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitergum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[542,709,661,687]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. albitergum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[716,806,661,687]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having darkly pigmented and sclerotized T3–6.
</paragraph>
